        <svcproc svcproctype="afcrepair" graphiccount="2">
            <title>SERVICE PROCEDURE</title>
            <para>The vehicles listed above will have the oil cooler mounted to the front crossmember with either plate
                "A" or plates "A" and "B" (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f9590601">Figure 1</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f9590601" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g9590601" filename="../afcfigures/g9590601.webp" type="webp" resolution="300"/>
                <caption>Figure 1.</caption>
            </figure>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>It is not necessary to disconnect the transmission oil cooler lines to change the mounting
                        bracket.
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the transmission oil cooler from the oil cooler mounting. Remove the mount from
                    the front crossmember (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f9590601">Figure 1</hotlnk>). Retain the fasteners, some of them will be re-used.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Mount the new one piece transmission oil cooler mounting bracket to the front
                    crossmember with four (4) 3/8 inch-16 x 1 inch grd 8 hex hd bolts, 3/8 inch lock nuts and flat
                    washers (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f9590602">Figure 2</hotlnk>).
                </para>
                <figure id="f9590602" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="g9590602" filename="../afcfigures/g9590602.webp" type="webp" resolution="300"/>
                    <caption>Figure 2.</caption>
                    <calloutgroup>
                        <callout1>1. BOLT, HEX HD 3/8 INCH-16 X 1 INCH. 3/8 INCH-16 LOCK NUT AND 3/8 INCH FLAT WASHER
                        </callout1>
                        <callout1>2. BOLT, HEX HD 3/8 INCH-16 X 1-1/2 INCHES. 3/8 INCH-16 LOCK NUT AND 3/8 INCH FLAT
                            WASHER
                        </callout1>
                    </calloutgroup>
                </figure>
            </step1>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>On vehicles that have dual steering gears, the hydraulic lines for the slave gear are mounted
                        to the bottom side of the crossmember with P-clamps. It will be necessary to mount the new
                        bracket between the hydraulic lines and the crossmember. Mount the hydraulic lines to the bottom
                        side of the mounting bracket with the same P-clamps.
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Mount the transmission oil cooler to the mounting bracket with four (4) 3/8 inch-16 x
                    1-1/2 inch grd 8 hex hd bolts, 3/8 inch lock nuts and flat washers (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f9590602">Figure 2</hotlnk>).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Tighten all fasteners to 34-38 ft-lbs. (46-51 Nm).</para>
            </step1>
        </svcproc>
